-- Credit Agricole’s Maioli Among Candidates as BPM CEO, Sole Says
-- B y   S o n i a   S i r l e t t i
-- 2011-12-21T06:57:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-21/credit-agricole-s-maioli-among-candidates-as-bpm-ceo-sole-says.html
Giampiero Maioli, chief executive
officer of  Credit Agricole SA (ACA) ’s Italian unit, Cariparma, is
among five candidates running for the top job at  Banca Popolare
di Milano Scarl (PMI) ,  Il Sole 24 Ore  reported, without saying how it
obtained the information.  Piero Montani, CEO of Banca del Sud, Gianemilio Osculati
and Giuseppe Castagna, managers at  Intesa Sanpaolo SpA (ISP) , and
 Banco Popolare SC (BP) ’s Maurizio Di Maio are the other candidates,
Il Sole said.  The Milan-based bank is seeking to fill a new CEO position
created after it changed its governance in September.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sonia Sirletti in Milan at 
 ssirletti@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Frank Connelly at   fconnelly@bloomberg.net  